Under the above conditions using Connect-AzAccount will throw
Could not load file or assembly 'Azure.Core, Version=1.9.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=92742159e12e44c8'. The system cannot find the file specified.

However, I can use the same command in Visual Studio Code PowerShell for 7 (and ISE for 5.1)
If I uninstall Azure.Storage.Blobs the call works as expected

I can toggle back and forth between seeing the above error and the code working by installing and uninstalling Azure.Storage.Blobs.

## Steps to reproduce
Setup an Azure Account
Setup a Service Principal (service username/password)
Execute Connect-AzAccount -ServicePrincipal (with other required parameters)

With Azure.Storage.Blobs installed, ps.Streams.Error will contain an error with the text above. Without Azure.Storage.Blobs the AzAccount connection works as expected.

How to setup a service principal (powershell)
```
